data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and its fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö no longer accepts expression trees

The setters parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code **won't compile**. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All that `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö two sub-changes

**a) Same-named properties are now uniquified.** If `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` both have `Street`, EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street1`) instead of silently sharing one column. To preserve the old shared-column behavior, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use full path in column names.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **If you have existing migrations**, both changes will generate a migration that renames columns. Either pin the old names as shown, or apply the migration to rename them in the DB.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
